Extracted from: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-40161?focusedCommentId=681336&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-681336

Now, when I try to create a worklog against an issue that may have hundreds of other worklogs against it, upon hitting the "Log Work" button in the Log Work dialogue box the browser doesn't show any action or movement for about 5-7 seconds (the browser doesn't look like anything has been done, there is no "working" spinning icon in the browser tab for example), and then suddenly refreshes and displays the page after an additional 3 seconds. The "paused" browser behavior is new - it was not doing this before - and it is also occurring on other issues that do not have a large amount of work logs associated with them.

The screen is loading faster than before (total of 10 seconds, rather than 25+ seconds) but the lack of activity in the browser window is slightly confusing and leads you to believe nothing is occurring, when in fact processing is occurring in the background.

