When viewing a ticket, click on the summary to edit. The field turns into an input so new text can be provided, but the input field behaves like a text area where only 1 line is visible at a time. That is, text is scrolled vertically. This makes it *very* difficult to edit a multi-line summary.
For example: Let's say a story has the summary: "As a student, I can see my grades online so that I don't have to wait until I get to school to know whether I'm passing" If I edit the summary then I see an input field that does not show the entire text. I see the text "As a student, I can see my grades online so" with the cursor at the beginning (window width determines how much text is visible). If I move the cursor to the end of the text field (hit end key) then the cursor is at 'so' and I have to hit the down or right key to be able to see the 2nd line of text.

Ideally I would be able to see a multi-line input so I could clearly see what I'm editing, but I would settle at least for normal behavior of an input field where text is scrolled horizontally rather than vertically.

