Right now, when performing a Bugzilla import in JIRA, there is the option to configure which status will be moved into which. Since the statuses are already mapped, it seems like it should be a good idea to let the customers choose which issues they want to move from each project and which they don't. We could do this based on the issue current status on Bugzilla.

h4. Steps to Reproduce the Problem:
# Restore the backup attached (JIRA 6.3.11) - [^add_watchers.zip];
There are three users:
#* admin/admin (with Browse Users permission)
#* user/user
#* customer/customer
# Log in as *user*;
# Create an issue;
# Add 'admin' as watcher through the issue view;
# Create another issue;
# Add 'admin' as watcher through the issue view;

*Alternatively*:
3. Access an issue through the 'Issues » Recently Viewed' menu;
4. Add 'admin' as watcher;
5. Access another issues directly through the menu;
6. Add 'admin' as watcher.

h4. Expected Behavior:
'admin' would be added as a watcher in all occasions.

h4. Actual Behavior
'admin' is only added as a watcher in the issues loaded first. See the attached video: [^add_watchers.mov]

+*Notes:*+
* It seems the problem happens because a JavaScript or AJAX function is only loaded the first time. When loading another issue from a view issue screen, it seems some resources are not reloaded. 
* This only happens when the user does not have 'Browse Users' global permission.
